                <h4 class="kicker">Your sentiments</h4>
                <h1>Are parking ticket fines in L.A. too high?</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="text collapse">
                <p><span class="credits">Produced by <a href="https://twitter.com/Evie_xing" target="blank">Evie Liu</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.scpr.org/about/people/staff/chris-keller">Chris Keller</a></span> | <span class="pubdate">Published June 10, 2014</span></p>
                <p>Have you ever gotten hit with a parking ticket for failing to feed a meter?</p>
                <p>At least one LA group says those parking ticket fines are too high in Los Angeles and is working to change things.</p>
                <p>Members of the LA Parking Freedom Initiative are pushing proposals to reform how the city manages parking. They propose capping the parking meter fine at $23, which is the median pay in the LA region for an hour. </p>
                <p>What's you opinion about parking in L.A.? Do you find the parking tickets fine too high for what you earn? Are the street parking signs clear enough for you to understand? Or they are part of the reason why you got a ticket? Share with us your parking frustration in L.A.!  </p>
